<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 06 at 5:47AM CDT until May 06 at 6:15AM CDT by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 615 AM CDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN COVINGTON COUNTY...
At 547 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 5 miles east of Andalusia to 8 miles southwest of Opp
to near Florala to 7 miles south of Lockhart, moving northeast at 50
mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Opp, Florala and Lockhart.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
